  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- United States: Bank Secrecy Act\n- European Union: Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- United Kingdom: Proceeds of Crime Act\n- Most countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws\n\n3. Key Components of AML Frameworks:\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Record-keeping regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n- International information sharing mechanisms\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Financial penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Banking license revocation\n\n5. Regulatory Bodies:\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Financial regulators\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds and integrating them into the legitimate financial system.\n\nWould you like more details about any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
